# Local test-result write-ups that quote raw log lines. These are working
# artefacts, not versioned docs — and because they paste journalctl output
# verbatim they can contain credentials. This one held a (since-rotated) Groq
# API key and was caught by GitHub push protection on 2026-07-18.
# NOTE: docs/tests/ and docs/audits/ are deliberately NOT ignored wholesale —
# 5 files in them ARE tracked (v0.35.2 results, integration test plan, audits).
docs/tests/results/v0.35.3-followup-test-results-2026-05-05.md

# Workflow-command run artefacts (agentic loops — see docs/LOOPS.md).
# These are local scratch/continuity outputs, not versioned docs:
#   incoming/*-runs/    — per-command run buffers (e.g. /fix, /qa working sets)
#   incoming/handovers/ — H2 interruption stop-state (gitignored; H3 lives in docs/handovers/)
#   incoming/docs/      — staging area if a standalone /docs command is later built
incoming/*-runs/
incoming/handovers/
incoming/docs/
